my:Hazard.my:ControlMeasures:
a) Use of suitable and appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, hard hat, gloves, etc.; 
b) Permission must be obtained from Master and / or Chief Engineer; 
c) Safe Work Permit to be issued; 
d) A safety harness with a lifeline or fall arrest equipment must be worn; 
e) A safety net should be rigged where necessary and appropriate; 
f) All equipment to be used i.e. safety harness, securing line, fall arrest should be visually inspected before use; 
g) Maintenance and inspections to be carried out in accordance with the Manufacturer's Manual and Company MPM system; 
h) The crew member aloft should be under observation from a person on deck. 
i) The crew should not work overboard whilst the vessel is underway 
j) The crew member overboard should be under observation from a person on deck.

a) All crew in the vicinity to wear suitable and appropriate PPE: overalls, safety shoes, hard hat, gloves, etc.; 
b) Suitable warning notices should be posted; 
c) Access to the area must be restricted when certain tasks i.e. welding aloft, etc. are carried out; 
d) A tool belt, designed to hold essential tools, should be worn - Tools should not be carried in pockets; 
e) Tools and stores should be sent up and lowered by line in suitable containers which should be secured in place for stowage of tools or materials; 
f) Tools should be handled with extra care when hands are cold and greasy and where the tools themselves are greasy; 
g) Consult 'Hot Work' Risk Assessment, if required; 
h) Consult ‘Operating Handheld Tools and Powered Tools’, if required; 
i) Consult 'Maintenance / Repair of Electrical Equipment' Risk Assessment, if required.

a) Working in the vicinity of radio antennas, the officer responsible should inform the bridge team so that no transmissions; 
b) Working in the vicinity of the radar scanner, the officer responsible should inform the bridge team so that the radar and scanner are isolated; 
c) Suitable warning notices should be posted on the bridge.
